summary:
The Security Council, 
Taking note of letters from the Secretary-General and the President of the International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda, 
Recalling resolutions 955 (1994), 1165 (1998), 1329 (2000), 1411 (2002), 1431 (2002), 1717 (2006), 1824 (2008), 1855 (2008), and 1878 (2009), 
Recalling the International Tribunal's Completion Strategy and its projected trial schedule, 
Convinced of the need to extend the authorization for additional ad litem judges, 
Urging the International Tribunal to complete its work expeditiously, 

1. Intends to extend trial judges' terms until 30 June 2010 and appeals judges' terms until 31 December 2012, or until case completion; 
2. Authorizes the temporary increase of ad litem judges to 12, returning to 9 by 31 December 2010; 
